Aim:Basic operation on image



matlab
1. Program to change the Brightness of Image.
2. To Flip the image around the vertical and horizontal line.
3. Display the color components of the image.
4. Display of gray scale images.
5. To find the negative of an image.

code:

% Load image
I = imread('beamer.jpg');

% 1. Program to change the Brightness of Image.
I1 = I - 50;
figure, imshow(I1);
I2 = I + 50;
figure, imshow(I2);

% 2. To Flip the image around the vertical and horizontal line.
% DISPLAY THE ORIGINAL AND FLIPPED IMAGE
j = fliplr(I); % Corrected from flipIr
k = flipud(I);
figure, imshow(I), title('Original Image');
figure, imshow(j), title('Flipped Horizontally');
figure, imshow(k), title('Flipped Vertically');

% 3. Display the color components of the image.
redChannel = I(:, :, 1); % Corrected extra semicolon
greenChannel = I(:, :, 2);
blueChannel = I(:, :, 3);
figure, imshow(redChannel), colormap([[0:1/255:1]', zeros(256,1), zeros(256,1)]), colorbar;
figure, imshow(greenChannel), colormap([zeros(256,1), [0:1/255:1]', zeros(256,1)]), colorbar;
figure, imshow(blueChannel), colormap([zeros(256,1), zeros(256,1), [0:1/255:1]']), colorbar;

% 4. Display of gray scale images.
a = im2gray(I);
figure, imshow(a); % Added from the second image

% 5. To find the negative of an image.
neg = 255 - I; % For uint8 images
figure, imshow(neg);
